The '''Watersportbaan''' is a [[rowing]] race course in the [[Belgian]] city of [[Ghent]]. It is 2300 meters long and 76 meters wide (just a 5-lane rowing course) and in 1954 was first used. Despite that most major international [[FISA]] - regattas are now equipped to 8-lane rowing jobs Albano format, this is a race track for 2 medium-sized international [[FISA]] selection - Regatta, but also for smaller competitions. The main medium-sized crowd-pullers are the annual Spring Regatta (Spring Regatta) and Meiregatta ([[May - Regatta]]), both extremely popular in [[England]] (named) and some other neighboring countries. Other exceptions to the [[FISA]] indication is the [[Henley Royal Regatta]] (only 2 lanes). Especially that matches on both sides may be close and the full last 250m stretch open seats are available. Unique to this urban facility near the city center is the direct connection with the numerous adjoining rivers and canals such as the Cuopure(Gent) the Graslei, the [[Ghent-Bruges Canal]] and the Lys (river), of which a side arm also flows through the rowing course. This makes them more attractive to students - and recreational boating. 

The Watersportbaan was a great and remarkable urbanization project in the old [[Ghent]] Neermeersen after the Second World War. The part to the 1500 line was already a part of the [[Lys(river)]]. The current ending was a dump and was so full remediated. The project consisted of social housing, which meanwhile is protected as odd, a small shopping center, schools and as a central element Watersportbaan. That was the original name 'Geo Nachez', to the deputy and club chairman from that time. The excavated soil the marshy Meersen were muted. The job was created for the [[European Championships Rowing]] in Ghent of [[1955]]. It is today a haven for various athletes. There are water sports such as rowing and kanopolo practiced. By both Civil youth rowing and a new [[Ghent Students Rowing]]. 

Around the track is a Finnish track of 5000 m constructed that is often used by joggers. Besides Watersportbaan are the recreation area and the [[Blaarmeersen]] and the famous International Indoor [[Ghent Topsporthal]].

